Knowledge as an expiring asset really puts things into perspective. What you know today becomes less valuable
as development continues. Well, at least the specific things do. The process of knowledge accumulation and
past experience has to continue to count for something.

Knowledge Portfolio Strategy
 - invest regularly
 - diversity
 - manage risk (conservative vs. high risk)
 - buy low, sell high
 - review and rebalance
 
 Knowledge Portfolio Prescription
  - Learn at least one new programming language every year
  - Read a technical book each quarter
  - Read non-technical books too
  - Take classes
  - Participate in local user groups
  - Experiment with different environments
  - Stay current (trade magazines and journals)
